cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper discusses user behavior and activity patterns in online systems, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on user behavior and its implications for system design. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely, as the paper discusses metrics for web analytics and behavioral analyses of user-facing systems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possibility, as the paper analyzes user activity across different domains of online activity. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but could be relevant if the paper discusses natural language processing or text analysis of user activity. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses the implications of user behavior for system design and theories of goal-directed human activity.
